The paper deals with video classification and activity recognition, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of state machines and dynamic programming also suggests a focus on algorithms and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of surgical datasets and surveillance videos suggests a potential application in medical imaging (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
